title: Solar wind proton and alpha parameters, including anisotropic temperatures, derived by non-linear fitting of the measurements and with moment techniques. Data in RTN - Bennett Maruca (University of Delaware)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/wind/swe/swe_h1_rtn/1994/wi_h1_swe_rtn_19941117_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 73.5450% of the 139 timesteps. Cadence = 74642 [ms] = PT1M14.642S.
